The paper discusses a probabilistic RSSI-based fingerprinting location determination system for GSM phones. This involves wireless network communication and signal processing, which falls under the category of Network and Information Theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the challenges of implementing the system, which could fall under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) or Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also evaluates the effect of changing system parameters, which could fall under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) or Information Theory (cs.IT).
